      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BOULEVARD BART (6) took on the good three-year-olds at the end of his maiden campaign but had shown promise when kicking off his career with a Maryborough win over this distance. Likely to have developed with maturity and three trial wins should have him ready to go. BREATHE EASY (5) has the hoof on the till after seconds in his last three outings, going under by narrow margins in his last two. Could break through. SHAZZA LOVE (8) had put together a string of top-four finishes before an easy last-start win at Charlton. Draws for a trail and could go on with it. PRICILLA (4) has been consistent since her debut win and is suited dropping to a distance where she has recorded a win and a placing in two attempts. CAPTAINS RUSH (11) overcame a similar draw to this to break her maiden at Geelong last week. Could take the next step.",
